# Regular tetrahedron, 4 triangle faces — the simplest possible
# demonstration of Combobulate's triangle rendering path.
#
# Vertices are placed at alternating corners of a unit cube
# (the classic inscribed-tetrahedron construction):
#
#   v1 = ( 1,  1,  1)
#   v2 = ( 1, -1, -1)
#   v3 = (-1,  1, -1)
#   v4 = (-1, -1,  1)
#
# Edge length = 2*sqrt(2) ≈ 2.83. Each face is an equilateral triangle.
#
# Every face is wound CCW so that (V1-V0) × (V2-V0) points outward (away
# from the centroid at the origin), satisfying Combobulate's back-face
# culling convention.
#
# No two faces are coplanar, so the quad-recovery preprocess cannot fuse
# any of them — the geometry ends up as four triangle CachedQuads that
# all render through the triangle clip + 3-point affine brush path. This
# is the smallest mesh that exercises that path end-to-end.

v  1  1  1   # 1
v  1 -1 -1   # 2
v -1  1 -1   # 3
v -1 -1  1   # 4

# Face opposite v4
f 1 2 3
# Face opposite v3
f 1 4 2
# Face opposite v2
f 1 3 4
# Face opposite v1
f 2 4 3
